---------------- version release check -------------------
1. normal play cpu usage.
2. update static library
3. remove debug info and change debug level
4. test new function added
5. stable test: loop play test one night

------------------------------------------------------------

usage for release user of android:
	1. check CedarX-Projects/Config.mk variable CEDARX_DEBUG := n
	2. when you compile for android, and if you modify any code, compile the library; 
       then run CedarAndroidLib/collect_libs.sh, then recompile the CedarX library.
       you may touch any CedarXAndroid file to guarantee the compile up to date.
   
usage for release user of linux:
	1. goto the dir of CedarX-Projects then run shell command "source env_setup.sh"
	2. edit CedarX-Projects/Makefile, and config CEDARX_DEBUG_LEVER to L2
	2. make clean && make
	

